{"word":"ἀζήμιος","slug":"ἀζήμιος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀζήμιος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ζημία'><el>ζημία</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>free from further payment: without loss, scot-free</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>immunis</el>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—<i>unpunished, not deserving punishment</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> <i>harmless</i>, of sour looks, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}